    "_body_text": "Hi Carolyn,\nQuick question: do they need to know which need data for testing the initial installation or whether they will need it at all (ie once the lab is up and running)? I think we could test connections to gases for some of these instruments without data, but probably want the data connection for transferring files when the instruments are actually in use.\nI added Luke Marney to this message to make sure we get this right. Luke: we can chat offline to figure out what's needed.\nBest,\nDoug\nOn Dec 14, 2020, at 3:22 PM, Stenbak, Carolyn <stenbakc@seattleu.edu<mailto:stenbakc@seattleu.edu>> wrote:\nHi Ryan and Doug,\nI know I sent this list to you earlier to confirm that we can find a way to move these pieces of equipment by May 7th to be installed in the new building. Thank you for your response and willingness to make it work.\nA related question has come up about which (if any) of these instruments require data connection. Could you please look at this list one more time and indicate which instruments need data?\nThanks for your help,\nCarolyn\nCarolyn Stenbak, Ph.D. | Associate Professor\nDEPARTMENT OF BIOLOGY | SEATTLE UNIVERSITY\n901 12th Avenue, Seattle, WA 98122-1090\n(206) 398-4376\n<Outlook-1502218874.png>\n<20201029_Owner Equipment List - Installed Before TCO.pdf>",

        "_message_body": "Hi Carolyn,\nQuick question: do they need to know which need data for testing the initial installation or whether they will need it at all (ie once the lab is up and running)?     "_body_text": "Hi Luke,\nI hope you are doing well and staying healthy!\nThe College has started the process of working with Procurement Services to purchase equipment requested for the new building.     "_body_text": "Hi Luke:\nCould you do me a favor?  Ideally on Friday (tomorrow), if possible?\nThe architects of the new SINE building need a few photos and measurements from the current NMR room (Bannan 112A) to help with some design details in the new SINE building.\nCould please send the following items to the group who is on this email message?\n  1.  Measure the height of the liquid nitrogen dewar that lives in the NMR room?  We want to install shelves on the wall above the dewar and we want to confirm that there is enough space for the dewar below the shelves.  Also, how much space above above the dewar do you need before you hit the shelf when you are using the dewar?\n  2.  Can you take a few photos (close up and perspective) of the hooks we use to store the liquid helium and liquid nitrogen transfer lines in the NMR room?  We need to know what the hooks look like, how many hooks there are, and also how the lines sit on the hooks.  Can you also measure the distance between each pair of adjacent hooks, and the distance from the first hook to the last hook?  (My memory is that there are 3 hooks, is that correct?)\n  3.  Can you take a few photos of the system we have for seismic restraint of the NMR magnet?  We have three rock-climbing ropes that run from each of three eyelets on the NMR magnet to three eyelets that are anchored in the ceiling/beams/concrete in the room.  We need to see the anchored eyelets in the ceiling if you can get close enough to them for a decent photo.\nThanks so much!\nBest,\nPJ\nPJ Alaimo, Ph.D.  |  Professor and Department Chair\nDEPARTMENT OF CHEMISTRY  |  SEATTLE UNIVERSITY",

    "_body_text": "Hello Joe (and PJ),\nYou are receiving this email because your computer with Asset Tag # 15813, has been identified as meeting the requirements for this year's computer refresh program:\n\u00b7        Devices running Windows 7\n\u00b7        Lenovo devices\n\u00b7        Computers over 4 years old\n\u00b7        Any computer that we have been advised by ITS should be replaced due to performance or security\n\u00b7        Desktop computers\nIf you do not believe your computer should be eligible for refresh, please let me know.\nPlease respond by March 1, 2021 to this email with one of the options below:\n  *   Lenovo 13\" Laptop\n  *   Lenovo Yoga 13\u201d touchscreen\n  *   MacBook 13\u201d Air\nIn an effort to provide additional flexibility in this new remote work environment, the university standard is now laptops. I will be placing an order for your new laptop and docking station; the specs for both items are attached. In order to start this process, please send me your current computer information.  I need your assistance to gather this information.  Please send me the following screenshot, instructions listed below.\n1.      Computer with Asset Tag number listed above is the one being replaced and the computer returned to IT at the end of this process.\n2.      Do you need Admin Rights on your computer? Admin rights allow you to download or update software not provided by SU.  Admin Rights are given to you if it precludes you from doing your day to day job.  Standard computer updates are done by SU and do not require you to have Admin Rights. \u2013 I will request Admin Rights on your new computer once the computer is in your possession.\n3.      Please let me know what type of computer to order for you based on the options listed above.\n4.      You will be getting a hub/docking station to accommodate your peripherals (i.e. multiple screens, iPads, printers, etc.)\nThis new computer exchange process will be contactless; details are below.\n\u00b7        As orders are collected, the Program Manager will contact each customer to get office details, including the building and room number.\n\u00b7        A public safety officer will accompany the technician to deliver the device and leave in your office or secure location, then email the user to confirm the delivery has occurred.\n\u00b7        You will then go to your office at a time that is convenient to complete the setup process, transfer any files via OneDrive, and confirm the new computer is working as expected.\no   If you need assistance transferring your files to OneDrive prior to picking up the new computer, please open a ticket and schedule a remote support appointment.\n\u00b7        Take the new computer home and start your computer set-up.  Once this is done, You will then go to campus and return your old computer to your office and email me so I can get it picked up.  IT has agreed that this will take time, but we are all responsible for returning your old computer to ITS as soon as possible.\no   If your computer is not returned within 5 business days, ITS will stop all future deliveries to CSE.\n\u00b7        Send NEW computer properties to me.  I will follow-up with a reminder if I do not get it from you.\n If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to email me.\nBest  Regards,\nLorena Toledo-Eastey | Budget & Operations Coordinator\nCollege of Science and Engineering | SEATTLE UNIVERSITY\n901 12th Avenue, Seattle, WA 98122-1090\nOffice (206) 296-5504 | ENGR 600",

        "_message_body": "Hello Joe (and PJ),\nYou are receiving this email because your computer with Asset Tag # 15813, has been identified as meeting the requirements for this year's computer refresh program:\n\u00b7        Devices running Windows 7\n\u00b7        Lenovo devices\n\u00b7        Computers over 4 years old\n\u00b7        Any computer that we have been advised by ITS should be replaced due to performance or security\n\u00b7        Desktop computers\nIf you do not believe your computer should be eligible for refresh, please let me know.\nPlease respond by March 1, 2021 to this email with one of the options below:\n  *   Lenovo 13\" Laptop\n  *   Lenovo Yoga 13\u201d touchscreen\n  *   MacBook 13\u201d Air\nIn an effort to provide additional flexibility in this new remote work environment, the university standard is now laptops. I will be placing an order for your new laptop and docking station; the specs for both items are attached. In order to start this process, please send me your current computer information.  I need your assistance to gather this information.  Please send me the following screenshot, instructions listed below.\n1.      Computer with Asset Tag number listed above is the one being replaced and the computer returned to IT at the end of this process.\n2.      Do you need Admin Rights on your computer? Admin rights allow you to download or update software not provided by SU.  Admin Rights are given to you if it precludes you from doing your day to day job.  Standard computer updates are done by SU and do not require you to have Admin Rights. \u2013 I will request Admin Rights on your new computer once the computer is in your possession.\n3.      Please let me know what type of computer to order for you based on the options listed above.\n4.      You will be getting a hub/docking station to accommodate your peripherals (i.e. multiple screens, iPads, printers, etc.)\nThis new computer exchange process will be contactless; details are below.\n\u00b7        As orders are collected, the Program Manager will contact each customer to get office details, including the building and room number.\n\u00b7        A public safety officer will accompany the technician to deliver the device and leave in your office or secure location, then email the user to confirm the delivery has occurred.\n\u00b7        You will then go to your office at a time that is convenient to complete the setup process, transfer any files via OneDrive, and confirm the new computer is working as expected.\no   If you need assistance transferring your files to OneDrive prior to picking up the new computer, please open a ticket and schedule a remote support appointment.\n\u00b7        Take the new computer home and start your computer set-up.  Once this is done, You will then go to campus and return your old computer to your office and email me so I can get it picked up.  IT has agreed that this will take time, but we are all responsible for returning your old computer to ITS as soon as possible.\no   If your computer is not returned within 5 business days, ITS will stop all future deliveries to CSE.\n\u00b7        Send NEW computer properties to me.  I will follow-up with a reminder if I do not get it from you.\n If you have any questions, please do not hesitate to email me.\nBest  Regards,\nLorena Toledo-Eastey | Budget & Operations Coordinator\nCollege of Science and Engineering | SEATTLE UNIVERSITY\n901 12th Avenue, Seattle, WA 98122-1090\nOffice (206) 296-5504 | ENGR 600",

    "_body_text": "Hi Luke:\nI have a few questions about the equipment moving list that you worked on.\n  *   Line numbers 223 and 224 on the MS Excel spreadsheet are items that you added from my research lab (a rotovap and a chiller), but you gave no voltage on the spreadsheet.  Can you check these please?  I think the chiller might be 220V, but I am unsure.  The rotovap has multiple electrical sources (3-4) that I THINK are all 115V, but I need you to confirm these.\n  *   Please let me know the final word on the glovebox.  Is it 220V or 115V?  We really need to get this corrected now.\n  *   The -70 freezer is a 5-20 plug.  Does that mean the voltage is 115V?  Or 220?  (Sorry I don't know more about electrical stuff.)\n  *   Also please let me know about the server.  Since it is loud, it would be great if it could go outside of our teaching and research space.     "_body_text": "Hello Luke,\nYou are receiving this email because your computer with Asset Tag # 17388, has been identified as meeting the requirements for this year's computer refresh program:\n  1.  Devices running windows 7\n  2.  Lenovo devices\n  3.  Computers over 4 years old\n  4.  Any computer that we have been advised by ITS should be replaced due to performance or security\n  5.  Desktop computers\nIf you do not believe your computer should be eligible for refresh, please let me know.\nIn an effort to provide additional flexibility in this new remote work environment, the university standard is now laptops. I will be placing an order for your new laptop and docking station, the specs for these items are attached. In order to start this process, please send me your current computer information.  I need your assistance to gather this information.  Please send me the following screen shot, instructions listed below.\n  1.  Computer Info Needed:\n*Go to the start menu of your computer and start typing\u2013 system information, select system information \u2013 this will be a pop-up with all computer information needed.\n            *Go to the email I sent, hit reply, then click on INSERT, click dropdown on Screenshot, and either use the Screen clipping tool or choose the picture to insert .\n*Send me the screen shot\n  1.  Do you need Admin Rights on your computer? admin rights allow you to download or update software not provided by SU.  Admin Rights are given to you if it precludes you from doing your day to day job.  Standard computer updates are done by SU and do not require you to have Admin Rights.\nAs soon as I receive this information, I will place the order for your Lenovo X13 Gen 1 and the docking station.  Please note that once I place your order, IT will begin the ordering and exchange process in order to get you your new laptop to you as quickly as possible.   This new computer exchange process will be contactless; details are below.\n  *   As orders are collected, the Program Manager will contact each customer to get office details including the building and room number.\n  *   A public safety officer will accompany the technician to deliver the device and will leave in your office or secure location, then email the user to confirm the delivery has occurred.\n  1.  You will then go to your office at a time that is convenient to complete the setup process, transfer any files via OneDrive, and confirm the new computer is working as expected.\n     *   If you need assistance transferring your files to OneDrive prior to picking up new computer, please open a ticket and schedule a remote support appointment.\n  1.  You will leave your old computer at work and email me so I may return it to ITS within 5 business days.\n     *   If your computer is not returned within 5 business days, ITS will stop all future deliveries to CSE.\n  1.  Send NEW computer properties to me.  I will follow-up with a reminder if I do not get it from you.\nIf you have any questions, please do not hesitate to email me.\nBest  Regards,\nLorena Toledo-Eastey | Budget & Operations Coordinator\nCollege of Science and Engineering | SEATTLE UNIVERSITY\n901 12th Avenue, Seattle, WA 98122-1090\nOffice (206) 296-5504 | ENGR 600",

        "_message_body": "Hello Luke,\nYou are receiving this email because your computer with Asset Tag # 17388, has been identified as meeting the requirements for this year's computer refresh program:\n  1.  Devices running windows 7\n  2.  Lenovo devices\n  3.  Computers over 4 years old\n  4.  Any computer that we have been advised by ITS should be replaced due to performance or security\n  5.  Desktop computers\nIf you do not believe your computer should be eligible for refresh, please let me know.\nIn an effort to provide additional flexibility in this new remote work environment, the university standard is now laptops. I will be placing an order for your new laptop and docking station, the specs for these items are attached. In order to start this process, please send me your current computer information.  I need your assistance to gather this information.  Please send me the following screen shot, instructions listed below.\n  1.  Computer Info Needed:\n*Go to the start menu of your computer and start typing\u2013 system information, select system information \u2013 this will be a pop-up with all computer information needed.\n            *Go to the email I sent, hit reply, then click on INSERT, click dropdown on Screenshot, and either use the Screen clipping tool or choose the picture to insert .\n*Send me the screen shot\n  1.  Do you need Admin Rights on your computer? admin rights allow you to download or update software not provided by SU.  Admin Rights are given to you if it precludes you from doing your day to day job.  Standard computer updates are done by SU and do not require you to have Admin Rights.\nAs soon as I receive this information, I will place the order for your Lenovo X13 Gen 1 and the docking station.  Please note that once I place your order, IT will begin the ordering and exchange process in order to get you your new laptop to you as quickly as possible.   This new computer exchange process will be contactless; details are below.\n  *   As orders are collected, the Program Manager will contact each customer to get office details including the building and room number.\n  *   A public safety officer will accompany the technician to deliver the device and will leave in your office or secure location, then email the user to confirm the delivery has occurred.\n  1.  You will then go to your office at a time that is convenient to complete the setup process, transfer any files via OneDrive, and confirm the new computer is working as expected.\n     *   If you need assistance transferring your files to OneDrive prior to picking up new computer, please open a ticket and schedule a remote support appointment.\n  1.  You will leave your old computer at work and email me so I may return it to ITS within 5 business days.\n     *   If your computer is not returned within 5 business days, ITS will stop all future deliveries to CSE.\n  1.  Send NEW computer properties to me.  I will follow-up with a reminder if I do not get it from you.\nIf you have any questions, please do not hesitate to email me.\nBest  Regards,\nLorena Toledo-Eastey | Budget & Operations Coordinator\nCollege of Science and Engineering | SEATTLE UNIVERSITY\n901 12th Avenue, Seattle, WA 98122-1090\nOffice (206) 296-5504 | ENGR 600",
